    <text id="B1063T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Waldo's last report before the Bureau ceased operations indicated no cases in
                    which injustice was committed.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Office 4th Division, 9th
                    Sub-District of Virginia.
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="General">Genl</abbr> O Brown<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Assistant">Asst</abbr> Commissioner<lb/>Richmond <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-12-31">December 31. 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>General:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>In compliance with Par 6 Circular No 10 - dated Head Quarters <abbr
                        expan="Assistant">Asst</abbr> Commmissioner Richmond <abbr expan="Virginia"
                        >Va</abbr> March 12, 1866 - in relation to the operation of the order
                    restoring to the Civil Authorities jurisdiction in Criminal Cases over Colored
                    persons &amp;c I have the honor to make the following report so far as said
                    order pertains to this Division (Highland and Augusta Counties).</p>

                <p>No case of a Criminal nature has been referred to the Civil Authorities from this
                    office during the past month, nor has any been tried by the Courts in which
                    there was any reason to believe that injustice was manifested toward any colored
                    party.</p>

                <p>As the Bureau closes its operations on this date, there seems to be no necessity
                    for extending this report, other than to refer to previous ones under this head.</p>

                <pb n="2"/>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="obedient">obt</abbr> servant</salute>
                    <signed>Roswell Waldo<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                            >A.S.A. Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
